Package: xtop
Version: 0.44.0-1
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Architecture: amd64
Depends: libc6
Recommends: postgresql, journalctl
Installed-Size: 23700
Maintainer: Farhan Tahir <farhan.003@gmail.com>
Homepage: https://github.com/ftahirops/xtop
Description: Incident-first root-cause analysis console for Linux
 v0.44.0 ships Guardian v2: per-collector cost attribution (EWMA mean,
 p95, alloc bytes), automatic disable of any collector that exceeds its
 budget for 3 consecutive ticks, soft+hard heap budgets per mode with
 cache-flush escalation and self-restart-via-systemd as last resort,
 audit log at ~/.xtop/guardian.log, and per-host self-resource fields
 (xtop CPU%, RSS MB, guard level, mode) on every fleet heartbeat.
 The web dashboard renders these as compact green/red chips on each
 host card so operators can audit "is xtop the problem?" at a glance.
